## 14. Collector Quadrants

### Hook: `hooks/useCollectorQuadrants.ts`
- React Query-based data fetching
- Query key: `["collector-quadrants", clientId, params]`
- Configurable params: quadrant filter, search, page, limit
- staleTime: 30s, gcTime: 5min, retry: 2

### Service: `getCollectorQuadrants()`
- `GET /v2/clients/${clientId}/managements/collector-quadrants`
- Query params: quadrant, search, page, limit
- Response: 6 quadrant arrays (broken_commitments, critical_debtors, cash_generation, deficient_technical_file, litigation, unclassified) + pagination

### Quadrant Types (`services/types.ts`):
```typescript
type QuadrantType = "BROKEN_COMMITMENTS" | "CRITICAL_DEBTORS" | "CASH_GENERATION" | "DEFICIENT_TECHNICAL_FILE" | "LITIGATION" | "UNCLASSIFIED" | null;
```

### QuadrantItem shape:
```typescript
interface QuadrantItem {
  debtorId: string;
  quadrant: string | null;
  quadrantName: string;
  debtor: { id, name, email, debtor_code, broken_commitments_count, broken_commitments_percentage, due_debt_amount };
}
```

### UI Usage:
- `TaskFilters` shows quadrant buttons with live counts
- `TasksList` renders quadrant sections with colored islands
- `DebtorSearchAutocomplete` searches across all quadrants
- `IndicatorsDebtor` shows management metrics in sidebar

